# Testing And Quality Gate Rule

- Always attempt to fix reported problems after edits.
- Prefer validating with targeted checks first, then full checks.
- Offer to run `yarn test:app` after modifications.
- For high-confidence changes, run broader validation (`yarn test:all`) when feasible.

## How to verify

- Confirm changed files have no new lint/type/test issues.
- Confirm `yarn test:app` was offered or executed after meaningful code edits.
- Confirm failures are addressed or explicitly documented with reason.
- Confirm no unrelated failing checks are hidden.
